# Netscape HTTP Cookie File
#
# This is a placeholder. To enable downloads, copy this file to `cookies.txt`
# (same folder) and replace its contents with a real cookie export from a
# logged-in YouTube session. `cookies.txt` is gitignored and must never be
# committed — it is a live credential for that account.
#
# How to export cookies is documented on the yt-dlp pages (search:
# "yt-dlp how do I pass cookies"). In short: log a throwaway/alt account into
# YouTube in a Firefox PRIVATE window, export with a "Get cookies.txt LOCALLY"
# extension, save as cookies.txt here, then close the window WITHOUT logging out.
#
# Lines below this point would be the actual cookie jar (one cookie per line).
